Tool Security Advisory (TSA) Specification
Copyright 2025 MCP Security Working Group

NOTICE AND DISCLAIMER
=====================

This specification and reference implementation are provided as an independent
community contribution to the Model Context Protocol (MCP) ecosystem security.

IMPORTANT DISCLAIMERS:

1. INDEPENDENT WORK: This specification is an independent community effort.
   It is NOT officially endorsed by, affiliated with, or maintained by
   Anthropic, the Model Context Protocol project, or any major technology
   provider unless explicitly stated otherwise.

2. NO WARRANTY: This specification and all accompanying tools are provided
   "AS IS" without warranty of any kind. The authors make no guarantees
   regarding the accuracy, completeness, or fitness for any particular
   purpose.

3. ADVISORY DATA: The sample advisories included in this package reference
   real CVEs verified against the National Vulnerability Database (NVD)
   and GitHub Security Advisories (GHSA). However, users should always
   verify vulnerability information against authoritative sources before
   making security decisions.

4. NOT LEGAL ADVICE: This specification does not constitute legal, security,
   or compliance advice. Organizations should consult appropriate experts
   before implementing security controls based on this specification.

5. EVOLVING STANDARD: This is version 1.0.0 of an evolving specification.
   Future versions may introduce breaking changes.

ATTRIBUTION
===========

This work builds upon and references the following standards and projects:

- JSON Schema (https://json-schema.org/) - Draft 2020-12
- OSV Schema (https://ossf.github.io/osv-schema/) - Open Source Vulnerability format
- CVSS (https://www.first.org/cvss/) - Common Vulnerability Scoring System
- RFC 8785 - JSON Canonicalization Scheme (JCS)
- Model Context Protocol (https://modelcontextprotocol.io/)

CVE DATA SOURCES
================

Advisory data verified against:
- National Vulnerability Database (NVD): https://nvd.nist.gov/
- GitHub Security Advisories (GHSA): https://github.com/advisories

CONTACT
=======

For questions, contributions, or security concerns regarding this
specification, please open an issue on the project repository.
